tldr: The user requested a review of a sleep questionnaire application and the
  implementation of missing features. The agent successfully added a tiredness
  severity scale, COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome detection, outbound
  resource links, weighted EDS scoring, expanded CSV export, and pain/chronic
  fatigue questions.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, requesting the implementation of any identified missing features.
  The agent conducted a detailed review against the Statement of Work and
  questionnaire specifications, identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently,
  the agent proceeded to implement these missing features. Key implementations
  included integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference with
  associated safety warnings, adding detection and tailored recommendations for
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome,
  incorporating placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health
  resources, and implementing a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS). Furthermore, the agent expanded the CSV export functionality
  to include all flattened questionnaire responses and introduced new questions
  for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening. These changes involved
  modifications across data types, validation schemas, React components for the
  questionnaire and report, and API routes for data export.
